# Aeonism: Sacred Geometry Temporal Engineering

Time is a design variable. Most civilizations fail to recognize this. The Gregorian calendar is not inevitable—it is a poor choice that conflicts with how consciousness actually develops.

Aeonism is the discipline of designing temporal systems that align with consciousness rather than against it.

## The Problem

Current time systems rest on arbitrary foundations. The 365.25-day year has no mathematical basis. Months vary in length without pattern. The entire system requires constant patching—leap years, leap seconds—to approximate reality.

More fundamentally, these systems treat time as a neutral container: "You get 24 hours per day, manage it." This ignores the actual fact that consciousness develops through recursion. You revisit patterns at higher awareness levels. Time should support this, not prevent it.

